{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":876,"text":"So, when I was in art school,"},{"time":2665,"text":"I developed a shake in my hand,"},{"time":4084,"text":"and this was the straightest line I could draw."},{"time":7116,"text":"Now in hindsight, it was actually good for some things,"},{"time":9767,"text":"like mixing a can of paint or shaking a Polaroid,"},{"time":12956,"text":"but at the time this was really doomsday."},{"time":15654,"text":"This was the destruction of my dream of becoming an artist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19271,"text":"The shake developed out of, really,"},{"time":21641,"text":"a single-minded pursuit of pointillism,"},{"time":23548,"text":"just years of making tiny, tiny dots."},{"time":26102,"text":"And eventually these dots went from being perfectly round"},{"time":29996,"text":"to looking more like tadpoles, because of the shake."},{"time":33684,"text":"So to compensate, I'd hold the pen tighter,"},{"time":35929,"text":"and this progressively made the shake worse,"},{"time":38244,"text":"so I'd hold the pen tighter still."},{"time":40516,"text":"And this became a vicious cycle that ended up"},{"time":42732,"text":"causing so much pain and joint issues,"},{"time":44956,"text":"I had trouble holding anything."},{"time":47172,"text":"And after spending all my life wanting to do art,"},{"time":50557,"text":"I left art school, and then I left art completely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55168,"text":"But after a few years, I just couldn't stay away from art,"},{"time":57628,"text":"and I decided to go to a neurologist about the shake"},{"time":59920,"text":"and discovered I had permanent nerve damage."},{"time":62780,"text":"And he actually took one look at my squiggly line,"},{"time":65509,"text":"and said, \"Well, why don't you just embrace the shake?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":68932,"text":"So I did. I went home, I grabbed a pencil,"},{"time":71542,"text":"and I just started letting my hand shake and shake."},{"time":73450,"text":"I was making all these scribble pictures."},{"time":75544,"text":"And even though it wasn't the kind of art"},{"time":77374,"text":"that I was ultimately passionate about, it felt great."},{"time":81030,"text":"And more importantly, once I embraced the shake,"},{"time":83509,"text":"I realized I could still make art."},{"time":85884,"text":"I just had to find a different approach"},{"time":87154,"text":"to making the art that I wanted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89507,"text":"Now, I still enjoyed the fragmentation of pointillism,"},{"time":92347,"text":"seeing these little tiny dots come together"},{"time":94176,"text":"to make this unified whole."},{"time":96157,"text":"So I began experimenting with other ways to fragment images"},{"time":99108,"text":"where the shake wouldn't affect the work,"},{"time":101286,"text":"like dipping my feet in paint and walking on a canvas,"},{"time":105763,"text":"or, in a 3D structure consisting of two-by-fours,"},{"time":109461,"text":"creating a 2D image by burning it with a blowtorch."},{"time":114924,"text":"I discovered that, if I worked on a larger scale and with bigger materials,"},{"time":118268,"text":"my hand really wouldn't hurt,"},{"time":120676,"text":"and after having gone from a single approach to art,"},{"time":124276,"text":"I ended up having an approach to creativity"},{"time":126527,"text":"that completely changed my artistic horizons."},{"time":130228,"text":"This was the first time I'd encountered this idea"},{"time":132148,"text":"that embracing a limitation could actually drive creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137620,"text":"At the time, I was finishing up school,"},{"time":140036,"text":"and I was so excited to get a real job and finally afford new art supplies."},{"time":143644,"text":"I had this horrible little set of tools, and I felt like"},{"time":147405,"text":"I could do so much more with the supplies"},{"time":149515,"text":"I thought an artist was supposed to have."},{"time":152047,"text":"I actually didn't even have a regular pair of scissors."},{"time":154252,"text":"I was using these metal shears until I stole a pair"},{"time":156764,"text":"from the office that I worked at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159012,"text":"So I got out of school, I got a job, I got a paycheck,"},{"time":161944,"text":"I got myself to the art store,"},{"time":163598,"text":"and I just went nuts buying supplies."},{"time":166712,"text":"And then when I got home, I sat down"},{"time":168340,"text":"and I set myself to task to really try to create something"},{"time":171448,"text":"just completely outside of the box."},{"time":174212,"text":"But I sat there for hours, and nothing came to mind."},{"time":178636,"text":"The same thing the next day, and then the next,"},{"time":181183,"text":"quickly slipping into a creative slump."},{"time":184872,"text":"And I was in a dark place for a long time, unable to create."},{"time":189120,"text":"And it didn't make any sense, because I was finally able"},{"time":191694,"text":"to support my art, and yet I was creatively blank."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196068,"text":"But as I searched around in the darkness,"},{"time":198280,"text":"I realized I was actually paralyzed by all of the choices"},{"time":201808,"text":"that I never had before."},{"time":204376,"text":"And it was then that I thought back to my jittery hands."},{"time":208099,"text":"Embrace the shake."},{"time":210816,"text":"And I realized, if I ever wanted my creativity back,"},{"time":213492,"text":"I had to quit trying so hard to think outside of the box"},{"time":217256,"text":"and get back into it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219972,"text":"I wondered, could you become more creative, then,"},{"time":222058,"text":"by looking for limitations?"},{"time":224956,"text":"What if I could only create with a dollar's worth of supplies?"},{"time":230137,"text":"At this point, I was spending a lot of my evenings in --"},{"time":232410,"text":"well, I guess I still spend a lot of my evenings in Starbucks —"},{"time":235183,"text":"but I know you can ask for an extra cup if you want one,"},{"time":238391,"text":"so I decided to ask for 50."},{"time":240784,"text":"Surprisingly, they just handed them right over,"},{"time":242567,"text":"and then with some pencils I already had,"},{"time":244555,"text":"I made this project for only 80 cents."},{"time":247735,"text":"It really became a moment of clarification for me"},{"time":250271,"text":"that we need to first be limited"},{"time":253151,"text":"in order to become limitless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256199,"text":"I took this approach of thinking inside the box"},{"time":258207,"text":"to my canvas, and wondered what if, instead of"},{"time":260110,"text":"painting on a canvas, I could only paint on my chest?"},{"time":263439,"text":"So I painted 30 images, one layer at a time,"},{"time":266023,"text":"one on top of another,"},{"time":267223,"text":"with each picture representing an influence in my life."},{"time":271723,"text":"Or what if, instead of painting with a brush,"},{"time":274375,"text":"I could only paint with karate chops? (Laughter)"},{"time":277127,"text":"So I'd dip my hands in paint,"},{"time":278603,"text":"and I just attacked the canvas,"},{"time":280023,"text":"and I actually hit so hard that I bruised a joint in my pinkie"},{"time":282732,"text":"and it was stuck straight for a couple of weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285664,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":289027,"text":"Or, what if instead of relying on myself,"},{"time":293232,"text":"I had to rely on other people"},{"time":295165,"text":"to create the content for the art?"},{"time":297817,"text":"So for six days, I lived in front of a webcam."},{"time":300608,"text":"I slept on the floor and I ate takeout,"},{"time":303248,"text":"and I asked people to call me and share a story with me"},{"time":305553,"text":"about a life-changing moment."},{"time":308236,"text":"Their stories became the art"},{"time":310688,"text":"as I wrote them onto the revolving canvas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314200,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":318665,"text":"Or what if instead of making art to display,"},{"time":323161,"text":"I had to destroy it?"},{"time":325424,"text":"This seemed like the ultimate limitation,"},{"time":327696,"text":"being an artist without art."},{"time":330188,"text":"This destruction idea turned into a yearlong project"},{"time":332736,"text":"that I called Goodbye Art,"},{"time":334089,"text":"where each and every piece of art had to be destroyed after its creation."},{"time":338785,"text":"In the beginning of Goodbye Art, I focused on"},{"time":340276,"text":"forced destruction, like this image of Jimi Hendrix,"},{"time":343003,"text":"made with over 7,000 matches."},{"time":345808,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":346974,"text":"Then I opened it up to creating art that was destroyed naturally."},{"time":350163,"text":"I looked for temporary materials,"},{"time":352776,"text":"like spitting out food --"},{"time":354950,"text":"(Laughter) —"},{"time":359012,"text":"sidewalk chalk"},{"time":362225,"text":"and even frozen wine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366761,"text":"The last iteration of destruction"},{"time":368822,"text":"was to try to produce something that didn't actually exist in the first place."},{"time":372865,"text":"So I organized candles on a table, I lit them, and then blew them out,"},{"time":376208,"text":"then repeated this process over and over with the same set of candles,"},{"time":379848,"text":"then assembled the videos into the larger image."},{"time":383761,"text":"So the end image was never visible as a physical whole."},{"time":388280,"text":"It was destroyed before it ever existed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392122,"text":"In the course of this Goodbye Art series,"},{"time":394608,"text":"I created 23 different pieces"},{"time":397440,"text":"with nothing left to physically display."},{"time":400752,"text":"What I thought would be the ultimate limitation"},{"time":403176,"text":"actually turned out to be the ultimate liberation,"},{"time":406104,"text":"as each time I created,"},{"time":408307,"text":"the destruction brought me back to a neutral place"},{"time":410319,"text":"where I felt refreshed and ready to start the next project."},{"time":414604,"text":"It did not happen overnight."},{"time":416960,"text":"There were times when my projects failed to get off the ground,"},{"time":419011,"text":"or, even worse, after spending tons of time on them"},{"time":421800,"text":"the end image was kind of embarrassing."},{"time":424312,"text":"But having committed to the process, I continued on,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427032,"text":"and something really surprising came out of this."},{"time":429043,"text":"As I destroyed each project,"},{"time":432009,"text":"I was learning to let go,"},{"time":434841,"text":"let go of outcomes, let go of failures,"},{"time":438352,"text":"and let go of imperfections."},{"time":440875,"text":"And in return, I found a process of creating art"},{"time":443304,"text":"that's perpetual and unencumbered by results."},{"time":447529,"text":"I found myself in a state of constant creation,"},{"time":449558,"text":"thinking only of what's next"},{"time":452056,"text":"and coming up with more ideas than ever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454952,"text":"When I think back to my three years away from art,"},{"time":457437,"text":"away from my dream, just going through the motions,"},{"time":460688,"text":"instead of trying to find a different way to continue that dream,"},{"time":464440,"text":"I just quit, I gave up."},{"time":467640,"text":"And what if I didn't embrace the shake?"},{"time":471256,"text":"Because embracing the shake for me"},{"time":472453,"text":"wasn't just about art and having art skills."},{"time":475093,"text":"It turned out to be about life, and having life skills."},{"time":479528,"text":"Because ultimately, most of what we do"},{"time":482039,"text":"takes place here, inside the box, with limited resources."},{"time":487611,"text":"Learning to be creative within the confines of our limitations"},{"time":491280,"text":"is the best hope we have to transform ourselves"},{"time":495359,"text":"and, collectively, transform our world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499224,"text":"Looking at limitations as a source of creativity"},{"time":503392,"text":"changed the course of my life."},{"time":506248,"text":"Now, when I run into a barrier"},{"time":507939,"text":"or I find myself creatively stumped,"},{"time":511048,"text":"I sometimes still struggle,"},{"time":512602,"text":"but I continue to show up for the process"},{"time":514696,"text":"and try to remind myself of the possibilities,"},{"time":518193,"text":"like using hundreds of real, live worms to make an image,"},{"time":522788,"text":"using a pushpin to tattoo a banana,"},{"time":527175,"text":"or painting a picture with hamburger grease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533198,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":535052,"text":"One of my most recent endeavors"},{"time":536659,"text":"is to try to translate the habits of creativity that I've learned"},{"time":540103,"text":"into something others can replicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543287,"text":"Limitations may be the most unlikely of places"},{"time":547144,"text":"to harness creativity, but perhaps"},{"time":550538,"text":"one of the best ways to get ourselves out of ruts,"},{"time":554208,"text":"rethink categories and challenge accepted norms."},{"time":558111,"text":"And instead of telling each other to seize the day,"},{"time":561970,"text":"maybe we can remind ourselves every day"},{"time":565933,"text":"to seize the limitation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568447,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569914,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}